Sanofi Paid Viehbacher EU3.61 Million in 2010, Up 3.9%

-- B y   P h i l   S e r a f i n o
-- 
2011-03-01T22:38:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/sanofi-paid-ceo-viehbacher-eu3-61-million-in-2010-up-3-9-.html
(Corrects first paragraph to show compensation was paid in
2010.)    Sanofi-Aventis SA  paid Chief
Executive Officer Chris Viehbacher 3.61 million euros ($4.99
million) in salary and bonus in 2010, up 3.9 percent from a year
earlier, the company said in a filing with the Securities and
Exchange Commission. Sanofi also awarded Viehbacher 2.5 million
euros of stock options.  The compensation Viehbacher received last year included 1.2
million euros in salary and a bonus of 2.4 million euros, the
filing showed. In 2009, he was paid a 1.2 million-euro salary
and a hiring bonus of 2.2 million euros, according to the
filing. He joined the company in December 2008.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  